1. Create AWS server. And enable ssh and http.

2. Connect to AWS server using putty

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mJaHARCfcA0

	- convert the pem file into ppk (private) using puttygen

	- load the ppk in putty, set user to ubuntu and set ip


2. Follow tutorial to install 

https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-set-up-a-node-js-application-for-production-on-ubuntu-16-04


3. Nodejs and Node may be different application. Use the following to symlink

https://github.com/nodejs/node-v0.x-archive/issues/3911

	sudo ln -s /usr/bin/nodejs /usr/bin/node

4. Git clone application on home directory. Then run NPM install

5. Install mongodb using following documents.

https://docs.mongodb.com/v3.2/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/

6. to update node application
	- log in using putty.
	- look for the node folder.
	- git pull origin master
	- npm or bower install to update
	- run "pm2 restart server"